    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="landing-section">
      <div class="landing-section-inner">
        <p class="section-label">Common Questions</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What is the Soleur thesis?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">The first billion-dollar company run by one person is an engineering problem, not a fantasy. Soleur solves it by deploying a full AI organization &mdash; {{ stats.agents }} agents across {{ stats.departments }} departments &mdash; that gives a single founder the operational capacity of a large company.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What is company-as-a-service?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Company-as-a-service is a platform model where AI agents operate as a full business organization across every department. Unlike individual AI assistants, a company-as-a-service platform shares knowledge across all departments and compounds institutional memory over time.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Is Soleur model-agnostic?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">The current implementation runs on Claude Code. The vision includes model-agnostic orchestration &mdash; selecting the best model for each task. The architecture is designed so the orchestration layer is independent of any single model provider.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What is the Soleur roadmap?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Three milestones define the roadmap. Milestone 1: automate software companies, giving one founder the leverage of a full organization. Milestone 2: extend orchestration to hardware companies and physical operations. Milestone 3: multiplanetary companies spanning off-world operations.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

